<section class="couple-styling-dresscodethemehomecoming section-dresscodethemehomecoming">
  <h2 class="section-title-dresscodethemehomecoming">Outfit Pairing Ideas for the Couple</h2>
  <div class="couple-style-wrapper-dresscodethemehomecoming">
    <img src="/img/pic 2.jpeg" alt="Couple styling" class="couple-image-dresscodethemehomecoming">
    <p>When selecting outfits for your homecoming celebration, consider the timeless elegance of coordination without going overboard with matching. The key is to find a balance between tradition and your personal style. Perhaps one of you can wear a traditional piece, while the other complements it with something more contemporary or subtle. Opt for colors that complement each other—think of rich tones like deep burgundy and gold, or soft pastels like blush pink and ivory—while allowing each individual’s personality to shine through. Layering textures, such as pairing a classic saree with modern accessories or a tailored suit with traditional jewelry, can create a harmonious blend of old and new. Remember, the most important part is feeling confident and comfortable in your chosen attire, creating a visual narrative that speaks to your unique bond while respecting the cultural significance of the event.</p>
  </div>
