  <div class="etiquette-grid-dresscodethemehomecoming">
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Avoid wearing full white (traditionally linked to mourning).</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Dress modestly if elders/traditional customs are expected.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Be mindful of the event’s color palette if there is one.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Skip overly flashy or heavily sequined outfits that may overshadow the hosts.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Consider wearing traditional attire to honor the cultural significance of the event.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Avoid casual wear like jeans, t-shirts, or sneakers unless the invite says otherwise.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Keep accessories minimal and elegant unless the occasion calls for festive bling.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Comfort matters—choose attire that allows ease of movement for socializing and dancing.</div>
    <div class="etiquette-card-dresscodethemehomecoming">Don’t forget grooming—neat hair, clean nails, and subtle fragrance go a long way.</div>
  </div>
